&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At EQT, you won&#39;t just do a job—you&#39;ll help shape our future. Through Transparent Leadership, you&#39;ll work alongside leaders who value collaboration and ensure every voice is heard. Through Connected Impact, you&#39;ll see how your work influences critical business decisions and drives value across our operations. Through Supported Growth, you&#39;ll have opportunities to expand your skills through cross-functional collaboration, development opportunities, and career advancement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Join our Qrew!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Automation Engineering Technician I/II/III role directly supports the Automation Engineering function through new project and maintenance construction/commissioning, execution of approved hardware/software changes, and providing technical support to field operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Automation Engineering Technician I/II/III&amp;nbsp;responsibilities include but are&amp;nbsp;not limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support compressor and pipeline facility commissioning tasks for new facility TILs and modifications of existing sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather onsite technical data for Automation Engineers and Compression Design Engineers related to capital project assignments, especially automated equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting engineers and operations with the specification, installation, and modification of automation systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install, configure, and calibrate automation equipment and control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting &amp;amp; Repair: Diagnose and fixing issues with automated and integrated systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with HMI &amp;amp; PLC software revisions and updates under direction from Automation Engineers (configuration, logic, displays, and security parameters).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement Cyber Security policies, including firmware and password updates on automation hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience and Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate’s degree in electrical, chemical, civil, mechanical, or petroleum engineering; or in math, science, or a closely related field. Equivalent military, vocational, or directly applicable work experience considered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driver’s license.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foundational knowledge of automation and control system concepts, fundamentals, and theory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intermediate computer/software skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective teamwork and communication abilities. Be self-motivated and willing to work individually or as a team member.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to adhere to predefined work plans and meet deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret electrical prints, P&amp;amp;ID, and block diagrams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand and troubleshoot PLC code, including Ladder logic, function block diagrams, and structured text.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate the ability to install industrial control devices and program motor controllers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Experience and Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 to 8+ years of increasing responsibility in automation, instrumentation, or controls, with demonstrated proficiency in PLCs, HMIs, and control systems.&lt;/li&gt;
