&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Join our Qrew!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The Pipeline Engineer II/III/Sr/Expert plays a critical role in delivering EQT’s midstream capital projects—from concept through commissioning. This position ensures that pipeline systems are designed and executed to meet the company’s standards for safety, reliability, efficiency, and environmental compliance. The engineer will integrate design, regulatory, construction, and operations inputs to develop technically sound and cost-effective solutions that enable EQT to move gas safely and efficiently to market.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Pipeline Engineer II/III/Sr/Expert responsibilities include but are not limited to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Engineering &amp;amp; Design Execution​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the technical design of gas gathering and transmission pipeline projects. Translate project scope and operational requirements into detailed design packages aligned with EQT specifications and industry standards. Support development of construction drawings, alignment sheets, and design documentation through collaboration with internal and external stakeholders.​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Delivery &amp;amp; Coordination​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with project managers to support all project phases - scoping, design, procurement, construction, and commissioning. Interface with land, regulatory, environmental, and operations teams to ensure design compliance and execution readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide engineering support during field construction and commissioning, resolving technical issues as they arise.​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regulatory &amp;amp; Environmental Stewardship​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all designs meet applicable codes, standards, and environmental regulations. Support permitting efforts and design modifications required for regulatory or environmental compliance.​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk Management &amp;amp; Technical Assurance​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify design and constructability risks early and recommend mitigation strategies. Champion design standardization, continuous improvement, and lessons-learned integration across EQT’s pipeline projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience and Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Civil, Mechanical, Petroleum, or Chemical (or related discipline)​.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in natural gas and/or natural gas pipeline or facility design. &amp;nbsp;​&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to

